@startuml Export Job Data Flow
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor User
participant "API Server" as API
database PostgreSQL
database Redis
participant "Worker Pod" as Worker
participant "BOP\n(User Validation)" as BOP
participant "Export Service" as Export
queue "Kafka" as Kafka
participant "Notifications\nService" as Notifications
participant "Email Service" as Email

== Job Creation ==
User -> API: POST /api/scheduler/v1/jobs\n{schedule: "0 9 * * *", type: "export", ...}
activate API
API -> API: Validate cron schedule
API -> PostgreSQL: INSERT INTO jobs\n(org_id, user_id, schedule, payload)
activate PostgreSQL
PostgreSQL --> API: Job created ✓
deactivate PostgreSQL
API -> Redis: Schedule job for execution
activate Redis
Redis --> API: Scheduled ✓
deactivate Redis
API --> User: 201 Created\n{job_id, next_run_at}
deactivate API

== Job Execution (Next Day at 9:00 AM) ==
Worker -> Redis: Get scheduled jobs
activate Worker
activate Redis
Redis --> Worker: [job-123]
deactivate Redis

Worker -> Redis: Acquire job lock
activate Redis
Redis --> Worker: Lock acquired ✓
deactivate Redis

Worker -> Redis: Get job definition
activate Redis
Redis --> Worker: Job details
deactivate Redis

== User Validation ==
Worker -> BOP: POST /api/users/validate\n{users: ["jdoe"]}
activate BOP
BOP --> Worker: {valid: true, org_id: "123", user_id: "456"}
deactivate BOP

== Export Execution ==
Worker -> Export: POST /api/export/v1/exports\n{name: "report.csv", format: "csv", filters: {...}}
activate Export
Export --> Worker: {export_id: "uuid-789",\nstatus: "pending"}
deactivate Export

loop Poll every 5 seconds (up to 60 times)
    Worker -> Export: GET /api/export/v1/exports/{uuid-789}
    activate Export
    Export --> Worker: {status: "processing"}
    deactivate Export
    Worker -> Worker: Sleep 5 seconds
end

Worker -> Export: GET /api/export/v1/exports/{uuid-789}
activate Export
Export --> Worker: {status: "complete",\nurl: "https://console.redhat.com/api/exports/v1/uuid/download"}
deactivate Export

== Save Results & Notify ==
Worker -> PostgreSQL: INSERT INTO job_runs\n(job_id, status: "success",\nresult: {export_url: "https://console.redhat.com/api/exports/v1/uuid/download"})
activate PostgreSQL
PostgreSQL --> Worker: Saved ✓
deactivate PostgreSQL

Worker -> Kafka: PRODUCE platform.notifications.ingress\n{bundle: "console",\nevent_type: "export-complete",\ncontext: {export_url, job_name}}
activate Kafka
Kafka --> Worker: Message sent ✓
deactivate Kafka

Worker -> Redis: Reschedule for next run
activate Redis
Redis --> Worker: Rescheduled ✓
deactivate Redis
Worker -> Redis: Release job lock
activate Redis
Redis --> Worker: Lock released ✓
deactivate Redis
deactivate Worker

== Notification Delivery ==
Kafka -> Notifications: Consume message\n{event: "export-complete", ...}
activate Notifications
Notifications -> Notifications: Look up user preferences
Notifications -> Email: Send email\nTo: user@example.com\nSubject: "Your export is ready"
activate Email
Email --> Notifications: Email queued ✓
deactivate Email
deactivate Notifications

== User Downloads Export ==
Email -> User: 📧 Email received\n"Your scheduled export 'Daily Report' is ready.\nClick to download: [Download Link]"
activate User
User -> Export: Click download link\nGET https://console.redhat.com/api/exports/v1/uuid/download
activate Export
Export --> User: report.csv\n(File downloaded) ✓
deactivate Export
deactivate User

@enduml
